msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "16. Eḷakalomasikkhāpada"
msgstr "16. The training rule on wool"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.16.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.90"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2176"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ "
"gacchantassa antarāmagge eḷakalomāni uppajjiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"At that time a certain monk who was walking through the Kosalan country on "
"his way to Sāvatthī obtained some wool."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so bhikkhu tāni eḷakalomāni uttarāsaṅgena bhaṇḍikaṃ bandhitvā "
"agamāsi."
msgstr "He bound it into a bundle with his upper robe and went on."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Manussā taṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā uppaṇḍesuṃ—"
msgstr "People who saw him mocked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "“kittakena te, bhante, kītāni?"
msgstr "“Venerable, how much did this cost you?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Kittako udayo bhavissatī”ti?"
msgstr "How much will the profit be?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "So bhikkhu tehi manussehi uppaṇḍiyamāno maṅku ahosi."
msgstr "As a result he was humiliated."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so bhikkhu sāvatthiṃ gantvā tāni eḷakalomāni ṭhitakova āsumbhi."
msgstr "When he arrived at Sāvatthī, he threw the wool to the ground."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks asked him"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, imāni eḷakalomāni ṭhitakova āsumbhasī”ti?"
msgstr "why."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"“Tathā hi panāhaṃ, āvuso, imesaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ kāraṇā manussehi uppaṇḍito”ti."
msgstr "“People have been mocking me because of this wool.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "“Kīva dūrato pana tvaṃ, āvuso, imāni eḷakalomāni āharī”ti?"
msgstr "“But how far have you carried it?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“Atirekatiyojanaṃ, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Over 40 kilometers.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.91"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu atirekatiyojanaṃ eḷakalomāni āharissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can a monk carry wool more than 40 kilometers?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2177"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato "
"etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing that monk in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, atirekatiyojanaṃ eḷakalomāni āharī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, atirekatiyojanaṃ eḷakalomāni āharissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you carry wool more than 40 kilometers?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Netaṃ moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2178"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: addhānamaggappaṭipannassa → … magga­paṭi­pannassa (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "“Bhikkhuno paneva addhānamaggappaṭipannassa eḷakalomāni uppajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If wool is given to a monk who is traveling, he may receive it if he wishes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamānena bhikkhunā paṭiggahetabbāni."
msgstr "If he receives it"

#. Three <i lang="pli">yojanas</i>. The length of a <i lang="pli">yojana</i> is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable estimate is 8 miles or approximately 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus 3 <i lang="pli">yojanas</i> is close to 40 km, which seems like a suitably round number given the uncertainty in the estimate.
#. VAR: haritabbāni → hāretabbāni (si, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "Paṭiggahetvā tiyojanaparamaṃ sahatthā haritabbāni, asante hārake."
msgstr ""
"and there is no one else to carry it, he may carry it himself for at most 40 "
"kilometers."

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "Tato ce uttari hareyya, asantepi hārake, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"If he carries it further than that, even if there is no one else to carry "
"it, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "(<em>16</em>:<strong>35</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.234"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.16.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2179"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Bhikkhuno paneva addhānamaggappaṭipannassāti"
msgstr "To a monk who is traveling:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "panthaṃ gacchantassa."
msgstr "one walking on a road."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2180"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Eḷakalomāni uppajjeyyunti"
msgstr "If wool is given:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.4"
msgid ""
"uppajjeyyuṃ saṃghato vā gaṇato vā ñātito vā mittato vā paṃsukūlaṃ vā attano "
"vā dhanena."
msgstr ""
"if it is given by the Order, by a group, by a relative, by a friend, or if "
"it is discarded wool, or if it is by means of his own property."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2181"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamānenāti"
msgstr "If he wishes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "icchamānena paṭiggahetabbāni."
msgstr "if he desires, he may receive it."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2182"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Paṭiggahetvā tiyojanaparamaṃ sahatthā haritabbānīti"
msgstr ""
"If he receives it […] he may carry it himself for at most 40 kilometers:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "tiyojanaparamatā sahatthā haritabbāni."
msgstr "he may carry it himself no further than 40 kilometers."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2183"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Asante hāraketi"
msgstr "There is no one else to carry it:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "nāñño koci hārako hoti itthī vā puriso vā gahaṭṭho vā pabbajito vā."
msgstr ""
"there is no other person who can carry it, either a woman or a man, either a "
"lay person or a monastic."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2184"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Tato ce uttari hareyya, asantepi hāraketi"
msgstr ""
"If he carries it further than that, even if there is no one else to carry it:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ tiyojanaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"when he goes beyond 40 kilometers with the first foot, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.92"></a> 
#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyāni honti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When he goes beyond with the second foot, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyāni honti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Antotiyojane ṭhito bahitiyojanaṃ pāteti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he stands within the 40 kilometer limit, but drops it beyond the 40 "
"kilometer limit, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.15"
msgid ""
"Aññassa yāne vā bhaṇḍe vā ajānantassa pakkhipitvā tiyojanaṃ atikkāmeti, "
"nissaggiyāni honti."
msgstr ""
"If he places it in the vehicle or among the goods of another without their "
"knowledge, and it goes more than 40 kilometers, it becomes subject to "
"relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "Nissajjitabbāni saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The wool should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbāni …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "“imāni me, bhante, eḷakalomāni tiyojanaṃ atikkāmitāni nissaggiyāni."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this wool which I have taken more than 40 kilometers is to be "
"relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Imānāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this wool back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2185"></a> 
#. VAR: atirekasaññī atikkāmeti → tiyojanaṃ atikkāmeti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Atirekatiyojane atirekasaññī atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he takes it more than 40 kilometers and he perceives it as more, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. VAR: vematiko atikkāmeti → tiyojanaṃ atikkāmeti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "Atirekatiyojane vematiko atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he takes it more than 40 kilometers, but he is unsure if he has, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. VAR: ūnakasaññī atikkāmeti → tiyojanaṃ atikkāmeti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Atirekatiyojane ūnakasaññī atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he takes it more than 40 kilometers, but he perceives it as less, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2186"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "Ūnakatiyojane atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he takes it less than 40 kilometers, but he perceives it as more, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Ūnakatiyojane vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he takes it less than 40 kilometers, but he is unsure if he has, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "Ūnakatiyojane ūnakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he takes it less than 40 kilometers and he perceives it as less, there is "
"no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2187"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "tiyojanaṃ harati,"
msgstr "if he carries it 40 kilometers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "ūnakatiyojanaṃ harati,"
msgstr "if he carries it less than 40 kilometers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "tiyojanaṃ haratipi,"
msgstr "if he carries it 40 kilometers and then carries it back;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "paccāharatipi,"
msgstr ""
"if he takes it 40 kilometers with the intention of staying there, but then "
"takes it further;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "tiyojanaṃ vāsādhippāyo gantvā tato paraṃ harati,"
msgstr "if he gets back what had been taken from him and then carries it on;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "acchinnaṃ paṭilabhitvā harati,"
msgstr "if he gets back what he had given up and then carries it on;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.93"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "nissaṭṭhaṃ paṭilabhitvā harati,"
msgstr "if he get someone else to carry it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.38"
msgid "aññaṃ harāpeti katabhaṇḍaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is a finished article;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.39"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.40"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2188"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np16:pts-cs2.41"
msgid "Eḷakalomasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on wool, is finished."

